EXTRACTED VALUE: Gun may not showcase the true power of the Xbox 360, it is still one slick open-ended shooter that does justice to the Western theme.
Beautiful Katamari includes few surprises, but it does offer up more of the enchanting gameplay and charming atmosphere the series is known for.
Blowing stuff up with a buddy absolutely rocks, but the AI is anything but intelligent and the graphics are a bit disappointing.
Blazing Angels has nice looks, but the action doesn't distinguish itself in any way.
You can literally jump into a game for fifteen minutes and find satisfaction.
Cinemotion allows a better view of the action whilst still showing you the ice surrounding you.
